The plane crashed minutes after taking off from Hilton on its way to the Umkomaas Airstrip in Southern KwaZulu-Natal. JOHANNESBURG - Two men have been killed in a light aircraft crash in Hilton, KwaZulu-Natal. The plane crashed minutes after taking off from Hilton on its way to the Umkomaas Airstrip in Southern KwaZulu-Natal. READ: Pilot killed after plane crashes into North West houses The country's Civil Aviation Authority is probing the accident. CAA members are on the ground collecting evidence. They are expected to release a preliminary report within the next 30 days.